{
  "texts": [
    "assay descriptions were manually inspected and analyzed.",
    "Molecules whose inhibitory constant (K i) was lower than 1 μM on reliable inhibition assays (CHEMBL3412886, CHEMBL917079) were retained.",
    "SMILES canonicalization and removal of stereochemistry and duplicates led to a set of 68 unique SMILES strings for fine-tuning (SMILES strings available in the dedicated GitHub repository).",
    "Model fine-tuning and de novo design.",
    "The fine-tuning dataset was split into ten train and validation splits (80-20%) to find the optimal number of fine-tuning epochs."
  ]
